  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best way to get change for the new 2000 INR note?",
  "response": "Exchanging a new \u20b92000 INR note for smaller denominations can be straightforward if you follow the appropriate steps. Here are the best ways to obtain change for your \u20b92000 note:\n\n### 1. **Visit Your Bank Branch**\n\n**Steps:**\n- **Go to Your Own Bank:** Visit the branch where you hold an account. Banks are typically more willing to assist their customers with exchanging large denominations.\n- **Speak to a Teller or Customer Service:** Explain that you need to break a \u20b92000 note into smaller denominations.\n- **Identification:** Carry a valid photo ID (like Aadhaar, PAN card, or passport) as some banks may require it for large transactions.\n- **Transaction Limits:** Be aware that some banks might have daily limits on the number of high-denomination notes they can exchange, so it might help to visit during off-peak hours or on a weekday.\n\n### 2. **Use ATMs (Limited Option)**\nWhile most ATMs do not dispense \u20b92000 notes, you can withdraw smaller amounts in various denominations:\n- **Withdraw Smaller Bills:** Use your debit or credit card to withdraw amounts that can be dispensed in smaller notes (\u20b9200, \u20b9500, etc.).\n- **Combine Withdrawals:** If you need specific denominations, you might need to make multiple withdrawals.\n\n### 3. **Visit Other Bank Branches**\nIf your primary bank cannot assist:\n- **Go to a Different Bank:** Many banks, especially major ones like SBI, HDFC, ICICI, Axis, and others, may offer to exchange \u20b92000 notes even if you don\u2019t have an account with them.\n- **Provide Identification:** Ensure you have your ID with you as banks will need to verify your identity.\n\n### 4. **Exchange at Authorized Currency Exchange Centers**\nSome authorized currency exchange centers or kiosks in malls and popular areas may assist in exchanging higher denomination notes, though this is less common for domestic currency like INR. Always ensure that the center is legitimate to avoid counterfeit risks.\n\n### 5. **Utilize Digital Transactions**\nIf breaking the note physically is challenging, consider converting it to digital form and then withdrawing smaller amounts:\n- **Deposit into Bank Account:** Deposit the \u20b92000 note into your bank account through a bank branch or an ATM that accepts deposits.\n- **Transfer Funds Digitally:** Use online banking or UPI services to transfer money to another account.\n- **Withdraw Smaller Amounts:** Withdraw the desired smaller denominations from an ATM.\n\n### 6. **Retail Outlets and Local Businesses**\nWhile not guaranteed, some larger retail stores or businesses might be willing to break a \u20b92000 note, especially if you are making a purchase:\n- **Make a Purchase:** Buy items totaling \u20b92000 and request change for the note.\n- **Check Their Policy:** Some businesses may have policies limiting the denominations they can accept or the amount of change they can provide.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n- **Plan Ahead:** Large denominations might not be as widely accepted for smaller transactions, so plan accordingly.\n- **Safety First:** Avoid trying to exchange large amounts of cash in unsecured or unfamiliar locations to prevent potential scams.\n- **Stay Updated:** Policies and available services can change, so it\u2019s a good idea to check with your bank for the latest information regarding exchanging large notes.\n\nBy following these methods, you should be able to effectively exchange your \u20b92000 INR note for smaller denominations with ease and security.",
